betterquesting:10.desc:8: §7As you awaken from your cryosleep, the familiar hum of the atmosphere regulators greets you.. and nothing else. The lab appears completely empty, the scientists and medics who were supposed to be on hand to assess you after your deep sleep nowhere to be seen. Perhaps this datapad can help you. You just need to turn it on...

§a> ...

> P.A.D. booting... wireless network not found....

> Falling back into emergency mode....

§§§bHello, <userid not found>, and welcome to the Long-Term 'Hybrid Experimental Living' Deep-Space Station -Niflheim-.  In the event of a possible station system failure, this PAD is programmed to boot into an emergency troubleshooting mode to assist crew members or station visitors with restoring functionality. In potentially catastrophic situations, this device is also capable of analysing its surroundings in order to guide the user through possible survival strategies. 

The rest is up to you.

§bThis PAD is equipped with state of the art visual and auditory recognition, motion detection, gas spectroscopy, barometric, gravimetric, chronometric, electromagnetic and radiometric sensors - and equally state of the art analysis software - in order to sample and analyse any manner of known phenomenom. However, due to various laws of physics, this PAD must be in close physical proximity to subjects, materials or phenomena.

Please examine this area manually for signs of life or, otherwise, recent activity.

§bAnalysis: No life signs detected and, additionally, sufficient time has passed since this area was used to render any biological remnants undetectable. Further inspection of the station will be required.

Note: life support equipment is issuing a warning that it is past its service date, and may malfunction. In the event of atmosphere regulator malfunction, try turning the vent pump off and then back on, remove the vent from the pump system and replace it, or move to a room that is oxygenated and then back again to attempt to jumpstart pump systems.

§I§f§k§l§f§lIf you find your oxygen meter dropping after entering the game in an area that should be sealed, you will need to find your area's Oxygen Vent and switch through its redstone settings to essentially turn it off and back on again. If this doesn't work, break it and then replace it - make sure you set the redstone settings to Inverted or Ignored, as default settings require a redstone signal such as from a lever.

§bNiflheim Station's command and communication center can be accessed through the living quarters. Station network servers will be located there, and physical access will allow for troubleshooting, while signs of activity may be present in the living quarters themselves.

§bDue to a lack of network connection, this PAD's internal clock cannot be synced and may be incorrect. In the event that a large period of time has passed since this station was previously occupied, it would be prudent to take stock of what food supplies remain in the station's refrigerated storage.

§bAccording to records, Niflheim Station posesses a single scout vessel and an asteroid capture and general purpose transport vessel, alongside enough emergency pods for the evacuation of the full crew and visitors, if any. Please conduct a visual inspection to assess if any spacecraft remain.

Please note: the hanger itself is unpressurized.

§bWhen Niflheim Station was to be converted into a long-term space habitation experiment, mission control concluded that station crew could not expect continued psychological stability with such a spartan living environment. Thus a new asteroid was captured and tethered to the existing structure, in which facsimiles of natural environments were constructed. These so-called leisure domes would have been used extensively, and may contain clues about the crew's whereabouts. They can be accessed primarily by short-range teleporter.

Due to its later addition to the station, it is not directly integrated into the station's systems, and contains its own power generation.

§bStation analysis complete.

No lifesigns or signs of recent biological activity present anywhere in the station. All spacecraft absent. Significant damage has been dealt to the living quarters and station command, and the asteroid superstructure they were built into. All perishable food supplies have expired. Atmospheric regulators functioning within acceptable tolerances, but require servicing. Teleporter access to leisure complex non-functional, possibly due to power failure. This has become a survival situation; your survival may require accessing these areas.

Inspection of leisure complex will require an EVA. The airlock to the hanger should contain spare space suits. Engineers additionally use a special grappling device to safely maneuver around the outside of the station for performing maintenance, and one should aid you too.

§bBased upon trajectory projections calculated from the damage to the living quarters, a waypoint has been created to direct you to the most likely site of structural damage. Make your way to the outside of the station through the hanger launch corridor and make a visual inspection. The leisure complex is located in the large asteroid tethered to the rest of the complex - you would consider its orientation 'up'. You will need to use the grappling tool to reach it.

My records note that there is an oxygen recharge pad in a maintenance shed located on the surface of the hangar asteroid if you require more air.

§bWith power restored, return to the station and enter the leisure complex. Once inside, inspect the atmospheric vents to ensure full functionality. If any areas remain unpressurised, follow previous advice regarding troubleshooting them.

As this area was designed to simulate nature and provide a maximally pleasurable aesthetic for the crew, all trees, water plants and soil are completely natural and were especially transported from Earth to retain beneficial bacteria and fungus, and even supports simple farming. This complex will thus be the most suitable location to support your survival. Treat this space as your home, but never forget that it is not.

§bDue to the lack of materials that can feasibly be utilised by a single person with their bare hands, you will need to start from the very basics. Although time and a lack of air appears to have killed the trees in the arboretum and dried out the soil, do not give up hope. Collect as much wood as you can, and search the remaining branches for any seeds that may be viable.

The establishment of a stable source of food will be your immediate priority. With a source of food and water, you will be able to take the time you need to create a plan of escape, or wait for rescue.

§a> Error: sensor data does not correlate with internal calculations. Recalculating...

§bAnalysis of the wood you have collected ind&^$icates that it is freshly cut, living w@#$ood. Your discovery of liv%$ing plant matter has increased your predicted survival chances. P#$&p^&s-@#$##$%^ if the dried soil can be rej$%*(#uvenated @#$#%%^$seeds from grass&$#*(@#%

§a> Error: data corruption detected. Energy surge detected. Error.

> Error.

> ...

> ...

> ...

> Emergency helper program temporarily unavailable.

§7§Y§7You've done it: the impossible. With just a few drops of your blood you can turn a barren wasteland into a forest. The burn of the knife doesn't even seem to hurt anymore. Sure it leaves you weary, but you've now given yourself the ability to rest, eat, take stock.

But, as miraculous as this power is, that can't be all there is to it, right? You can feel that it isn't. There's something in your mind that was once locked and is no longer; You are starting to understand possibilities. You just need a foundation, a starting point.

That strange, floating flower and its power...

What if you made your own?

You just use the ashes to create a little binding circle, place within the item you want changed, then what you want to change it with, and...

§7This altar, it seems to do.. something with your blood. But what then? Will this life force-incarnate work away from the altar? What if you could carry its power with you?

Perhaps it's worth finding out.

§a> §aWarning: anomalous energy spike detected from flower-like object in proximity to dead wood. Energy source indeterminable. Unknown reaction occurring.

§bDue to increased radiation and electromagnetic flux being generated by the object, it is advised that you place it at least one meter away from yourself while analysis continues.

§7It's so simple. Life begets life. And the life you create is so powerful, full of infinite possibilities - even delicate little flower petals. The one who left the altar down in the depths of the station; did they have their own version of that flower you found? Did they follow this same path of discovery?

Perhaps they were reaching the same conclusions as you when the station was abandoned, forcing them to leave what they had created behind.

Where §odid§o§r§7 everyone go? Even if that thought itches at your mind, you can't stop now. Not if you're going to survive, surpass...

§a> . . .

> PAD bo@t se#uence initia$ed. ^rror checkin- ski%ped. Booting into <#%&#@*&$!> mode...

> Initiali@ed.

§bHello. Don't panic!

You are still alive. This is the most optimal possible situation considering the circumstances. Scans indicate that you may be anemic however. 

Analysing surroundings.... Evidence of basic farming detected. Warning: anomalous energy signatures have multiplied dramatically. Radiation levels are negligable, but exercise caution.

Calculations show that your attempt at farming is thus far extremely inefficient. Based on your available resources, I can recommend increasing yield through irrigation and soil fertilisation.

§7It's just a simple door. But why does it lack a mechanism to open it? What's back there in the darkness? You can't quite make it out, but curiosity gnaws at you. Maybe if you find a way to open it later, you can come back here...

§7Something feels...

Right.

You're probably just imagining it. But it's kinda funny, it's a simple little stone basin, but the features are fascinating. It feels so ancient, but pristine. And the craftsmanship on the stones at its base make it clear they go together. Perfectly.

Something like this requires pride of place in your living area. Somewhere you can see it. Somewhere you can be nearby it. Within reach, even.

There is one small flaw though. It could use a little more.. §cred§7.

§7That strange floating flower that knocked out your PAD had some sort of power inherent to it, something that renewed life in that which was dead around it. But it was a small, local effect. What if this basin, this.. altar has power too? It feels like it should, but it's.. inert. Waiting. It needs something. You can.. feel hidden power within far beyond that flower. It just needs.. you.

A small nick, just a trickle of blood. It won't kill you if you are careful.

Imagine what you could do with that power?
With a Seed Reprocessor, excess seeds from stat enhancing can be consumed to generate a small amount of essence. These do not need to be powered.
§7If you're going to be figuring what you're doing out, you're going to have to start taking notes. Best start from the beginning: creating paper, binding a book.

§7It wouldn't take a botanist to tell that these flowers you've brought to bloom are truly extraordinary. Especially so the odd sap that some produce, some use, and which has.. transformative properties. Their effects can only be described as magical.

There must be more you can do with this. Something more substantial. Just use that white flower to make a platform for your ingredients, add a little of the sap, and then...

You may have to survive here for some time, and that means a varied diet.

Spice of Life has been configured such that the 'food history' is time based; after a couple of days a food's sustenance will return to full after eating. To put it simply, the more you need to eat in a short period of time, the more variety you will need to make.

§7It worked! It worked flawlessly. But there is one more loop back to take.

The odd little pools where the sap condenses and collects, throwing things in changes them, makes them into versions more attuned with it. But as has been proven this substance is very versatile. If you could... tune the sap, perhaps you could make it change what is put into it even more drastically to create entirely new objects, or more.

Ideally this catalyst should go beneath the pool for maximum surface-area contact.

§bMy analysis suggests that some of your plants appear to be growing substances extremely close to the atomic makeup of valuable minerals. Ca-a-lcula%%$# errrrr-

§a> Erro% han#ling overr&4den. P$ogr#m resu*ed.

§bThe presence of workable materials, especially the minerals of iron, gold and redstone, open significant opportunities that dramatically increase your chances of survival to: possible, but still dubious. I have...

§oI§r§b have calculated a possible route you may take to gradually develop technology in a timeframe suited to your limited lifespan. The iron ingots you have smelted thus far are insufficiently dense and hard however. You may need to explosively correct this.

I recommend doing it from a distance.

§7If your blood can be used to infuse something with magically overabundant life, you can't help but wonder: could a method be tapped into to diffuse said power out into everything around you? It will surely be taxing on your blood supply, but it may be worth the cost...

To get the most out of your crops, you will need to know about crossbreeding and stat enhancing.

In order to produce some new crops, such as food seeds beyond the wheat and potatoes you get from grass, you will need to crossbreed them by placing the two parent crops with a space between them, and then placing down crop sticks with another set of crop sticks atop them - these are called §5cross sticks§f. Eventually a new plant will spread onto them, though it may take a few tries to get the one you want.

For stat enhancing, you will want to duplicate your initial seeds by letting them spread, until you have four. Then, place all four around a central space, and once all four are mature, place cross sticks in the middle. When a plant spawns in the middle, break it and take its seed to the §5Seed Analyzer§f to see its stats. You then replace one of the existing plants with it. You can continue with this until its stats are 10/10/10 for the most optimal production.

Note: crops will spread to single sticks, but without the chance of mutating higher stats.

A number of methods of speeding plant growth are available to you.

§5Worms§f from tilling grass till, water and slightly improve the growth of a 3x3 area they are planted on.
§5Red Fertilizer§f improves the growth of crops on blocks it is used on.
§5Bonemeal§f can't be used to speed up Mystical Agriculture crop growth directly, but it can be used on cross sticks to roll a chance for spreading to occur.
§

More methods will surely become available in time...

§7Even if your body becomes accustomed to the kiss of the blade to your flesh, having to slowly drain your life essence into the altar in order to stay above what you need to survive is a precarious prospect.

If you could only just focus, reach a level of understanding of your body such that with a single slice you could give exactly what is possible but no more. You've heard incense helps reaching such a state...

§bIn order to begin the arduous task of constructing appropriate technology in order to call for rescue or enact an escape, you will need to start simple. As you lack the tools and equipment to create such things as electronic components and circuitry, I.. I.. I have calculated based on my historical data that the most optimal method will be employing pressurized air. A more modern version of steam power.

I.. I...

User, please be advised that while my sensors do not detect any known harmful radiation, gravitational or magnetic fields from the present anomalies, they appear to be having an unknown effect on the PAD's circuitry and my.. my.. my programming.

You may find ways to harness or interface their energy with technology, but I cannot calculate the outcome of such.

§bWhile plastic may seem unimportant to a lay person, it is an vital first step towards forming more complicated substances and parts. For example, you will be able to use it as a non-conducting substrate in simple electronics such as resistors, capacitors and transistors. With gold and a method of etching circuitboards, you will have all you need to create your first electronic devices.

However, while you will need to do this initially with acid, this is a very hazardous and slow method. It will, however, be a necessary step to automating their production.
§bAlthough it may not be immediately helpful to you, accessing the maintenance substructure of the station may allow repairs to infrastructure systems if the need arises.

§bYour survival will require that you be diligent, observant, and most importantly that you salvage everything possible to support yourself. Make sure that you search the station for any potentially useful supplies, components or machines that you could make use of.

§7You have wood, you have seeds, you have soil and water. If you're going to eat, you're going to want to get started growing some food. Bonemeal will help fertilise the crops, and perhaps any excess crops can be recycled at a replicator for more supplies.

§bWith irrigation systems in place, your need for water has dramatically increased. A method of automating collection and dispersion will be necessary to reduce manual labour required. You can construct basic powered water pumps for this purpose. One to draw water from a source you have created, and one to pump it into the storage tanks of the irrigation system will be sufficient.

§8§7§7One pump will need to be placed directly above an infinite water source, and you will use the Hammer to create an Output (orange) port on one side of it. This will also need power (connected to the top) and a redstone signal such as a lever to activate. Pipes connected to the output port will then need to be run to the bottom of the second pump set level with your irrigation system. This too will need a side set to output into the water barrels, and a lever, but will not need to be powered.

§bAs you begin to create machines, you will need to work raw metals into sheets, rods and wires before they can be used. With a sturdy enough stone table and an engineer's hammer, you will be able to work ingots into plates for further processing. It will be a laborious process at first, but you will likely create a more efficient method before long.

§bI have been accessing records of your actions taken while I was offline. It appears you have been using some kind of anomalous-energy fluid to fundamentally reconfigure the molecular structure of materials and even form aggregate substances. I have found no previous record of this phenomenom. Exposure to the energy produced by these reactions appears to have introduced uncorrectable errors into both my hardware and software.. altering me.

Given the properties of the materials you have been working with however, I have hypothesised that you may be able to use it to create a material similar to steel in strength but as an insulator, both shielding electronics from the anomalous energy present, and containing it. A material such as this could be used to contain the pressures necessary to create simple machinery with extremely high stress tolerances.

§bWith your first circuit board, you can now build a process that will automate the production of further circuitry. This is an important breakthrough in your progression, and will enable a wide variety of more advanced machinery to be created.

Note however that these are still your first steps, and that your technology will be crude and bulky at first. Effective use of your space will be crucial until you can miniaturize your machine technology.

§bWith the ability to manufacture plastic and circuitry, an opportunity has opened up for you. As this station was created to study the effects of long term space habitation on living beings, a number of animal tissue samples would have been taken as a matter of the testing of said effects.

With these tissue samples, you may be able to fabricate meat and animal byproducts such as leather if you are able to create an appropriate biolattice scaffold and a grafting and maturing machine setup.

You may also consider uses of this emergence of technology for modernizing your farming.
betterquesting:10.name:8: The modern age (of meat and meat byproducts)

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
§a<§kasdoks;dlfks;dflkajs;dlfkadlfka;sldfkja;sldfkjas;dlfkja';lsdfa'lsdf;lkj;lakj;lkajsd;flkajs;dlfkja;sldkfja;slkdfja;lskdfj;alsdkfj;alskdfj;alskdfj;alskdfj;alskdjf;alskdfj;alskdfj;aslkdfj;alskfjd;alskdfj;alskdfj;alksdjf;laskdfj;alskdfj;asldkfj;asldkfj;asldkfja;sldkfja;sdlkfja;sldkfja;sldkfj;asldfkj;asdkjlf§a>

§c[You seek power.]

[You seek escape. You seek answers.]

[You have felt the brush of my mind before. Now that you have ventured away from your metal box, I can grasp it fully. Your little helper will be no use where you must go. I will... guide you.]

[You must be willing to do whatever it takes. Your mind must remain open.]

[Collect the crystals. You will know what to do then, as if instinct.]

§7Sure, you may have plenty of water available from the station's stores. But why carry buckets of it everywhere you go when you can just generate it at will, wherever it's needed? Granted, the water may be coming from your blood, but you're 70% water, you can spare a little!
Tired of vanilla chests? You've got a lot of options to choose from, with more increasing over time!
betterquesting:10.name:8: Where to put all your stuff

betterquesting:10.desc:8: §bWith this new technology, it would be prudent to enhance your ability to pressurise air by building an electrically powered compressor. Now that you have your first circuit boards available, this is a possibility for you to exploit.

§7The scent of the incense that focuses your mind and soul for bloodletting has become simply a part of your daily life by now. But it's gotten you thinking...

What if a potion could be infused into incense, healing you for as long as you're breathing in its vapour. The flower sap you've been using certainly has a knack for binding things together...

§7You would have never believed in things such as alchemy before. But now you're realising it's just another form of science that you're only now coming to understand. Odd concepts keep clicking in your mind, and then you realise how obvious they were.

Combine some ingredients, add a catalyst and a pinch of your essence, and you will have what you seek. It's so simple.

You can even picture in your mind what the worktable will be, what aparatuses you will need.

You found out very early on that sleeping in a bed isn't possible in microgravity. However, while the cryo stasis units are primarily used for what led you to this situation, they can be used simply as a sleeping pod as well.

§bHull breach found. Power cables appear to have been damaged, leading to power loss. Recommended action: use the station maintenance replicator to replicate new power cables in order to reconnect the internal lines leading from the station reactor to the power grid. The reactor is housed in the lowest section.

§b§a> Alert: unusual radiation detected from a small, transparent and hollow meteor fragment left in the wreckage. Output is not at dangerous levels, but further examination will be required. Radiation source appears to be the flower-like object within the hollow shell.

§bFor the convenience of the crew, a Matter Replicator was installed within the leisure complex so that their favourite refreshments could be analyzed for future replication. Although the process is slow and will significantly eat into your energy, you may also use it to scan items you wish to replicate.

For optimal replication data, 5 copies of each desired item will need to be analyzed. Please note that the replicator pattern storage has limited space.

§bReplicator systems like the one in the storage bay are vitally important for maintaining autonomy on a long-term station. Unneeded matter can be recycled in order to create needed equipment on-demand. Approach the terminal here and see what it has available; it may aid your situation.

Remember, your survival may depend on seeking resources, and exploring the station and its surroundings for anything you can possibly use later.
With copper available to fashion to your own ends, you'll be able to make the wiring and contacts required for charging the batteries of anything you have that uses electricity.

§bWith a structure to catalyse the coal you have obtained into oil, a wide new avenue of technological progression lays ahead of you. With even a small-scale refinery process, oil can be distilled into a number of hydrocarbons such as diesel fuel and liquid petroleum gas. This latter one will be the most important for your future endeavours, as it can be further processed into plastic. 

Note: you will need a method of heating the refinery enough to separate the oil into its component fluids, and a lot of air pressure. I suggest making multiple compressors. Alternatively, you could make a structure that heats the refinery with electricity instead.
§7Overwhelmed by all the various tools, wands and sigils you need to carry around? Perhaps this Omnimetal can help!

§7More than simply a platform for the basin, these stones around it appear to form some kind of altar structure, one that you feel will need to grow for your power to grow with it. This structure surely cannot be assembled haphazardly though. Curiously, this knowledge feels as though it has been within you your entire life, simply waiting to come out. So, allow it to.
betterquesting:10.name:8: Do you wanna build an altar?

betterquesting:10.desc:8: §bAs space is limited, rather than devoting ever-increasing amounts of it to the growing of your crops, you may consider hydroponics instead. While it may require some infrastructure, a hydroponic setup can dramatically improve the output of your crops. The addition of light lamps, CO2 diffusers and an aquaponics tank to add fertiliser to the water, along with automated collectors, can ensure you will have as much resources as you can possibly need.

§bWith the technology you have to begin with, an excessive buildup of pressure is an inevitable problem to deal with. To this end, you may wish to create and attach pressure release valves to your pipes to prevent catastrophic failures. The design I have created for you allows for fine control of the maximum allowed pressure through redstone power signals. You will want to keep the maximum pressure under 5 bar for now.

§b<Error found in internal maps>

My scans have detected a room behind the escape pod launch bay, with odd energy signatures, but it appears that section of the station was damaged and partially unpowered. I have marked a waypoint to its location.

§bWhile you have made an important step towards the technological requirements necessary to escape the station and search for the whereabouts of your crew and any other survivors of your race, your capabilities are still insufficient. Steel is an excellent material for building factories with, but you will need to gain access to more exotic elements in order to progress with developing more advanced technology.

Until these can be found, your progression is stalled here.

§bNo records exist in my databanks of this room or the ring structure in the space below. This must have been added to the station after my programming was completed. Analysis of the ring indicates that it is suffused with an unknown element, and uses technology entirely unlike anything humans have produced. It is, however, connected to human power and control systems. You should thus be able to use the computer to ascertain its purpose.

Note: this revelation has generated further questions of both what happened on this station after its conversion to a long-term living experiment, and exactly how much time has passed since.

§7When the computer is powered, right click on the computer case and click the power button to turn it on. It will automatically boot into the SGCX stargate control program. You will need to click the Asteroid address in the list to select it, and then Open Gate.

§bIt appears the ring is some kind of... gateway, forming a stable wormhole between two points in spacetime. I cannot determine where it leads, but it must be important to the crew. You are just going to have to investigate yourself.

§7You find ideas popping into your head, as if they were there all along and you are simply rediscovering them. Or perhaps as if you are intuiting them and they are simply natural. However, as thoughts turn to realizations of more and more possibilities, a particular thought presses itself into your mind.

§c[Dangerous. Do not underestimate this. Just as smoke chokes the air, wastefulness with this power pollutes the very essence of the space around you.]

§7The thought is accompanied by a feeling; a sense not of fear but of wariness, caution. You know that this power has strange effects on electronics, thus it likely would be better to conduct your experiments in a safe location, such as the asteroid you found the crystals in. At least until you better understand how to protect yourself and the station - or deal with the consequences.
You have awoken to an empty station. What now?
